<mxfile host="localhost">
  <diagram name="Page-1" id="B2aFiPByRvWryG6JL-6-">
    <mxGraphModel dx="1510" dy="996" grid="0" gridSize="10" guides="1" tooltips="1" connect="1" arrows="1" fold="1" page="1" pageScale="1" pageWidth="2000" pageHeight="1169" math="0" shadow="0">
      <root>
        <mxCell id="0" />
        <mxCell id="1" parent="0" />
        <mxCell id="title" parent="1" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=top;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;fontColor=#0C5BA6;" value="&lt;font style=&quot;font-size:26px&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;GottaGo: Solution Architecture&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;font-size: 14px; margin-top: 8px; color: rgb(51, 65, 79);&quot;&gt;GottaGo turns a battery-powered e-paper radiator into a glanceable “when do I leave?” display. A Cloudflare Worker resolves the active profile phase, pulls live departures from Metlink, renders a 1-bit BMP frame, and tells the radiator how long to deep-sleep before its next wake.&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="110" width="1360" x="76" y="201" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="steps" parent="1" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#f5f5f5;strokeColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacingLeft=16;spacingRight=14;spacingTop=14;fontColor=#333333;" value="&lt;b style=&quot;font-size: 15px; color: rgb(12, 91, 166);&quot;&gt;How it works&lt;/b&gt;&lt;ol style=&quot;font-size:13px;margin-top:12px;padding-left:18px;line-height:1.55&quot;&gt;&lt;li&gt;The &lt;b&gt;Radiator&lt;/b&gt; wakes on a timer and calls &lt;code&gt;GET /v1/frame&lt;/code&gt; over HTTPS — sending its slug, a bearer token, and battery telemetry.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;The &lt;b&gt;Worker&lt;/b&gt; resolves the active profile phase and fetches live departures from the &lt;b&gt;Metlink Stop Predictions API&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;For the calendar layout the Worker reads NZ public holidays from &lt;b&gt;Workers KV&lt;/b&gt; — used only to shade calendar days, and it soft-misses to an unshaded calendar if absent.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;The Worker renders the frame (Satori → 1-bit BMP) and returns the gzipped BMP plus an &lt;code&gt;X-Sleep-Seconds&lt;/code&gt; header; the Radiator flushes the panel and deep-sleeps. An unchanged frame returns &lt;code&gt;304&lt;/code&gt; and skips the flush.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="381" width="392" x="1139" y="285" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="bHome" parent="1" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;dashed=1;fillColor=none;strokeColor=#777777;verticalAlign=top;align=left;spacingLeft=8;spacingTop=4;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#555555;container=1;recursiveResize=0;collapsible=0;" value="Home / Office" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="237" width="240" x="76" y="365" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="radiator" parent="bHome" style="shape=image;verticalLabelPosition=bottom;labelBackgroundColor=none;verticalAlign=top;aspect=fixed;imageAspect=0;image=data:image/jpeg,;fontSize=12;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#333333;" value="Radiator&#xa;LilyGO T5 4.7&quot; e-paper · ESP32-S3" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="120" width="120" x="65" y="47" as="geometry" />
